cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper discusses a method for Collaborative Filtering (CF) using neural embedding algorithms, which falls under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Skip-gram with Negative Sampling (SGNS) and word2vec also suggests a connection to Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the method's ability to infer item-item relations without user information may also relate to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
